    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "A10512 - Igor Sikorsky's S-36 amphibian, launched in 1927, was the world's first practical amphibian\ntransport. Pan American Airways found it an ideal point from which to start development of its\nfamous line of flying boats.\nThirty-four feet long and with a wing-spread of 72-feet, the 100-mile~\nan-hour airplane was powered by two 200-horsepower engines.\nIt carried eight passengers,",
      "1927\nIGOR SIKORSKY'S S-36 AMPHIBIAN, LAUNCHED IN 1927 WAS THE WORLD'S\nFIRST PRACTICAL AMPHIBIAN TRANSPORT, PAA FOUND IT AN IDEAL POINT\nFROM WHICH TO START DEVELOPMENT OF ITS FAMOUS LINE OF FLYING BOATS.\nTHIRTY-FOUR FEET LONG AND WITH A WING-SPREAD OF 72-FEET, THE 100-\nMILE-AN-HOUR AIRPLANE WAS POWERED BY TWO 200-HORSEPOWER ENGINES.\nTHE S-36 CARRIED EIGHT PASSENGERS."
    ],
